indigo child there's been a lot of talk

underachievers

the song or rather that

evening most appealing thing about this

and he's got the sexy girl around him

and living in this magical tree out in
the forest so I can't really say I went
into this new Rory album with incredibly
high hopes because with these songs thus
far Rory has sounded like every bland
guitar strum er I've ever heard for the

Rory always seems to slip in these faint

articulate all the words just kind of
melt together it just sounds amateurish
and nothing of note really occurs
instrumentally most of the songs here

fine the beats are pretty well executed
for the most part there's just not
anything vocally chorus wise or
songwriting wise that I really see being
carried into next year there's no
definitive sonic style to the songs on
this record the songs on this record
drown in their own influences they sound
like they've been put together by
somebody who's relative
young and musically inexperienced
somebody who hasn't really had the time
or the opportunity to hone their own
musical thumbprint and this
